flowchart TD
    A([Start Production test run])
    A --> B[Create Production Order<br/>Status = Draft]
    B --> C{Any reserve on Draft?}
    C -->|No| C1[PASS PR-01]
    C -->|Yes| C2[FAIL PR-01]

    C1 --> D[Click Release]
    D --> E{Enough available stock to reserve?}
    E -->|No| E1[Error: insufficient raw material to reserve<br/>Status remains Draft<br/>PASS PR-03]
    E -->|Yes| E2[Create bill of materials snapshot + Reserve raw materials<br/>Status = Released<br/>PASS PR-02]

    E1 --> D
    E2 --> F[Verify stock_reservations<br/>reference = ProductionOrder]
    F --> G[Verify warehouse batch reserved_quantity]

    G --> H{Run Cancel Released scenario?}
    H -->|Yes| H1[Click Cancel]
    H1 --> H2[Reservation released<br/>reserved_quantity back to 0<br/>Status = Cancelled<br/>PASS PR-04]
    H2 --> Z([End Cancel branch])
    H -->|No| I[Create / open Production Batch]

    I --> J[Create raw material consumption lines]
    J --> K[Deduct raw materials from stock]
    K --> L{All order batches have posted raw materials?}
    L -->|No| L1[Reservation stays active<br/>Track PR-12]
    L -->|Yes| L2[Consume reservation<br/>reserved_quantity back to 0<br/>PASS PR-05]

    L1 --> M[Post next batch]
    M --> K
    L2 --> N[Order status moves to In progress]
    N --> O[Create manufactured product outputs]
    O --> P[Post finished goods receipt]
    P --> Q{Any manufactured product batch still unposted?}
    Q -->|Yes| O
    Q -->|No| R[Order status = Completed]

    R --> S[Material shortage summary validation]
    S --> T{Status filter}
    T -->|Draft| T1[Do not subtract Production Draft reserve<br/>PR-10]
    T -->|Released + In progress| T2[Available subtracts Production and delivery order reserve<br/>PR-11]
    T1 --> U([Test run completed])
    T2 --> U
